---
import BlogLayout from "../layouts/BlogLayout.astro";
import Header from "../components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
import SiteOptions from "../site.config.mjs";

const siteTitle = SiteOptions.siteTitle || "PlayTested";
---

<BlogLayout title={`About ${siteTitle}`} description={`${siteTitle} — how we review games, our scoring, tools, and disclosures.`}>
  <Header />

  <main class="mt-10 mb-16 space-y-12">
    <!-- Hero -->
    <section class="rounded-2xl p-8 bg-white dark:bg-slate-800 border border-gray-200 dark:border-slate-700">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-2">About {siteTitle}</h1>
      <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 max-w-8xl">
        <strong>PlayTested</strong> is a no-nonsense gaming review platform and tech blog. Objective, honest reviews that cut through the noise.
        <br /><br />
        <strong>PlayTested</strong> started as a personal passion project, born from my love of sharing honest game reviews. What started as a simple hobby soon grew into a real, paying role where I reviewed games almost daily, blending critique with insight into the industry. When that chapter eventually ended, I was determined not to let years of work fade away. In the spirit of preserving everything I’d created — and with a drive to learn more about web design and AI — <strong>PlayTested</strong> evolved into the site you see today.
      </p>

      <div class="mt-6 flex flex-wrap gap-3 text-sm">
        <a href="/category/review" class="px-3 py-1 rounded bg-blue-600 text-white">Read Reviews</a>
        <a href="/ai/recommend" class="px-3 py-1 rounded bg-slate-200 dark:bg-slate-700">AI Recommend</a>
        <a href="/ai/compare" class="px-3 py-1 rounded bg-slate-200 dark:bg-slate-700">AI Compare</a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Review Philosophy -->
    <section class="rounded-2xl p-8 bg-white dark:bg-slate-800 border border-gray-200 dark:border-slate-700">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-6 text-center">How We Review</h2>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
        <!-- Story & Pacing -->
        <div class="p-4 rounded-lg bg-gray-50 dark:bg-slate-900 border dark:border-slate-700">
          <h2 class="font-semibold mb-2">Story First</h2>
          <p>
            Main Story experience is our priority. Optional content is explored when it feels natural and enhances the game, not because a checklist or an achievement says so. We avoid grind for grind’s sake, but embrace side content that genuinely adds to the journey.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Timing & Context -->
        <div class="p-4 rounded-lg bg-gray-50 dark:bg-slate-900 border dark:border-slate-700">
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2">Patient Gamer... mostly</h3>
          <p>
            We sometimes review after patches, DLC context, and player meta settle — no rush reviews; no FOMO scoring. But if something truly excites us, we’ll jump in early.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Criteria -->
        <div class="p-4 rounded-lg bg-gray-50 dark:bg-slate-900 border dark:border-slate-700">
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2">What We Judge</h3>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1">
            <li>Gameplay systems and level design</li>
            <li>Narrative, characters, and worldbuilding</li>
            <li>Art direction, graphics, and audio</li>
            <li>Performance Notes (real-world use, not lab benchmarks)</li>
            <li>Time-to-fun and overall value</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Closing note -->
      <p class="mt-6 text-center text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 max-w-5xl mx-auto">
        The fact that we're playing it in the first place means the idea already hooked us; we will still judge it objectively and say when it doesn’t land.
        <br />
        Reviews are written with honesty, a player-first mindset, and the aim to help you decide if it’s worth your time.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Scoring -->
    <section class="rounded-2xl p-8 bg-gray-50 dark:bg-slate-800 border border-gray-200 dark:border-slate-700">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Scoring Guide</h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-5 gap-4 text-sm">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-lg bg-white dark:bg-slate-900 border dark:border-slate-700">
          <div class="text-2xl font-bold">9–10</div>
          <p>A Masterclass. Recommended to almost everyone. A must buy for those who like the genre.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-lg bg-white dark:bg-slate-900 border dark:border-slate-700">
          <div class="text-2xl font-bold">8–8.9</div>
          <p>Great. Strong buy for fans, easy recommend with minor caveats.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-lg bg-white dark:bg-slate-900 border dark:border-slate-700">
          <div class="text-2xl font-bold">7–7.9</div>
          <p>Good. Fun but flawed or niche. Wait for sale or subscription service if unsure.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-lg bg-white dark:bg-slate-900 border dark:border-slate-700">
          <div class="text-2xl font-bold">6–6.9</div>
          <p>Mixed. Specific audiences only. Consider heavy discounts or getting it as a freebie.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-lg bg-white dark:bg-slate-900 border dark:border-slate-700">
          <div class="text-2xl font-bold">&lt;6</div>
          <p>Skip unless you love the IP or a very specific mechanic, or the specific niche hits the right spot.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="mt-3 text-xs text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">
        Scores appear as a badge on post thumbnails and at the top of review articles.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- AI Tools -->
    <section class="rounded-2xl p-8 bg-white dark:bg-slate-800 border border-gray-200 dark:border-slate-700">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">AI Features</h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-1">AI Recommend</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">
            Pick up to five games you love and get smart suggestions with reasons you’ll likely vibe with them.
            We fetch covers and basics via RAWG, then run an explanation step so you see why each pick fits.
          </p>
          <a href="/ai/recommend" class="inline-block mt-3 px-3 py-1 rounded bg-blue-600 text-white text-sm">Try AI Recommend</a>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-1">AI Compare</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">
            Put two or more games side by side and get a clean breakdown of gameplay, story, and overall vibe to help you choose.
          </p>
          <a href="/ai/compare" class="inline-block mt-3 px-3 py-1 rounded bg-blue-600 text-white text-sm">Try AI Compare</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <hr class="my-6 border-gray-200 dark:border-slate-700" />

      <div class="flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-x-8 gap-y-4 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
        <div class="flex items-center space-x-2">
          <span class="w-2 h-2 bg-green-500 rounded-full"></span>
          <span>RAWG API Integration</span>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-center space-x-2">
          <span class="w-2 h-2 bg-blue-500 rounded-full"></span>
          <span>OpenRouter AI</span>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-center space-x-2">
          <span class="w-2 h-2 bg-red-500 rounded-full"></span>
          <span>Google Gemini Lite</span>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-center space-x-2">
          <span class="w-2 h-2 bg-purple-500 rounded-full"></span>
          <span>Real-time Analysis</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Disclosures -->
    <section class="rounded-2xl p-8 bg-white dark:bg-slate-800 border border-gray-200 dark:border-slate-700">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Disclosures & Ethics</h2>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 list-disc pl-5">
        <li>Review copies may be provided by publishers or purchased</li>
        <li>No paid positive reviews — opinions are independent</li>
        <li>Affiliate links, if present, will be clearly marked</li>
        <li>AI is used for assistive tasks like grammar checking and outline drafting; final reviews are human‑edited.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- Contact -->
    <section class="rounded-2xl p-4 bg-gray-50 dark:bg-slate-800 border border-gray-200 dark:border-slate-700">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-2">Contact</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
        For review codes, corrections, or collaboration, send a note to
        <a class="underline" href="mailto:lyndongaming@gmail.com">lyndongaming@gmail.com</a>. I'm still working on getting an official email soon.
      </p>
      <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mt-2">
        Based in Southeast Asia. Reviews are time‑zoned to UTC+08:00.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Site & Tech -->
    <section class="rounded-2xl p-4 bg-gray-50 dark:bg-slate-800 border border-gray-200 dark:border-slate-700">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-center">Site & Tech</h2>

      <div class="flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-x-8 gap-y-4 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
        <div class="flex items-center space-x-2">
          <span class="w-2 h-2 bg-blue-500 rounded-full"></span>
          <span>Astro + Tailwind</span>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-center space-x-2">
          <span class="w-2 h-2 bg-green-500 rounded-full"></span>
          <span>Cloudflare Pages Hosting</span>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-center space-x-2">
          <span class="w-2 h-2 bg-yellow-500 rounded-full"></span>
          <span>JSON Minisearch Index</span>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-center space-x-2">
          <span class="w-2 h-2 bg-purple-500 rounded-full"></span>
          <span>AVIF Optimized Images</span>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-center space-x-2">
          <span class="w-2 h-2 bg-pink-500 rounded-full"></span>
          <span>DecapCMS</span>
        </div>
                <div class="flex items-center space-x-2">
          <span class="w-2 h-2 bg-violet-500 rounded-full"></span>
          <span>Giscus comments</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <Footer />

  <!-- JSON‑LD (use set:html so it’s valid JSON to Google) -->
  <script
    type="application/ld+json"
    set:html={JSON.stringify({
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "WebSite",
      "name": siteTitle,
      "url": "https://playtested.net",
      "description": "Patient-gamer reviews with clear verdicts, scoring, and AI tools for recommendations and comparisons.",
      "inLanguage": "en",
      "publisher": {
        "@type": "Organization",
        "name": siteTitle
      }
    })}
  />
</BlogLayout>
